Poured from a 330 ml bottle.
Colour is light golden-yellow .&nbsp;
Minimal head which disappeared fast.
Aroma is of malts and hops.&nbsp;
Taste is bitter.&nbsp;
Thin in body on the palate and quite carbonated. The ABV was stated on the label to be 4.9% and not 5.

&lt;!-- i --&gt;Bottled.&lt;!-- /i --&gt;
Pale golden, large white head.
Sourish and grassy in both aroma and flavour. Some sweetish maltiness.
